The Chairman of the Ekiti State Judicial Commission of Inquiry on Lands and Related Matters, Justice Adekunle Adeleye, has ordered that two rooms out of the three-room apartment occupied by the Peace Corps, Ekiti State, be sealed off. The Peace Corps, during their appearance before the commission, admitted that no rent had been paid to the State Housing Corporation since 2016.  The Chairman of the Ekiti State Judicial Commission of Inquiry on Lands and Related Matters, Justice Adekunle Adeleye, has ordered that two rooms out of the three-room apartment occupied by the Peace Corps, Ekiti State, be sealed off. The Peace Corps, during their appearance before the commission, admitted that no rent had been paid to the State Housing Corporation since 2016. 